The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New York, June 22 (PTI): An Indian woman who threw her 19-month-old daughter into the Hudson river here and then jumped in herself has pleaded not guilty.          
	Devi Silvias lawyer argued that her act was a result of bipolar disorder, which she was recently diagnosed with. But the prosecutors have argued that she acted in such a way to take revenge on her husband. The baby survived but contracted hypothermia and was blue when rescued from the river.                   
	Islamabad (PTI): Pakistan will release 17 Indian prisoners on Wednesday as a goodwill gesture, officials said. The decision comes ahead of the meeting between the foreign secretaries of the two countries on June 24. Humanitarian issues are expected to figure in the talks.                  
	Vadodara (PTI): The Forest department has rescued a four-year-old leopard that had fallen into a 50-foot-deep well in a village in Junagadh, Gujarat. After a 13-hour effort, the animal was rescued using a net trap and was released into the Gir forest.                  
	Lucknow (PTI): The BSP is yet to decide the number of seats it will contest in the Bihar and Bengal Assembly polls scheduled later this year. BSP chief Mayavati had recently held discussions with party office-bearers on the preparations for the Assembly polls in the two states.                  
	Nagpur (PTI): Nagpur police have collected Rs 5 crore in fines on drunken drivers. The amount includes Rs 2 crore collected between January and May 2010. On an average about 2,000 cases of drunken driving are registered every month and around Rs 40 lakh are collected as penalty.                                                                                                                                              
